{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "992e085d-c103-48a8-a786-eb563594495f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1.What are Escape characters ? and how do you use them ?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "c06d3e84-88e3-4edc-95df-66f2b2cfe73b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans: Escape characters represent characters in string values that would otherwise be difficult or\n",
    "impossible to type into code. we can use the backslash `character` to escape a single character or symbol  \n",
    "**example:** `\\t, \\n`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "edcfd51b-7819-4f43-b8d8-24a41d908fce",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " 2.What do the escape characters n and t stand for ?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "fc549670-9f9e-41e9-8471-211fdea378ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans: `\\n` is a newline, `\\t` is a tab"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b3740e60-598e-4c00-b383-b75d1716e07b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " 3.What is the way to include backslash character in a string?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ff5f20ef-b514-4034-bfea-1411ec0e9661",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans: The `\\\\` escape character will represent the backslash character in a string"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b1c12668-e92c-443f-9592-8a26b1270960",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " 4.The string \"Howl's Moving Castle\" is a correct value. Why isn't the single quote character in the word Howl's not escaped a problem ?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "8d0a4a63-53d0-4452-acb0-e2d509a9553e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans:The string `\"Howl's Moving Castle\"` escaped the problem because it is wrapped inside double quotes.\n",
    "if its wrapped inside single quotes then we have to use escape character `\\'` to show single quote in the final output  \n",
    "`'Howl\\'s Moving Castle'` **`->`** `'Howl's Moving Castle'`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5e367b0a-41a7-49c1-b4ed-202a9eabdf99",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "5.How do you write a string of newlines if you don't want to use the n character?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d68c54af-1f3a-4642-889e-8f91fe3ea6de",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ans: Multiline string allow you to use newlines in string without the `\\n` escape character  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "de3b2f8a-adbd-4da6-9a95-8d02f7d3954b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "iNeuron full stack\n",
      "Data Science Course\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Example:\n",
    "a = '''iNeuron full stack\n",
    "Data Science Course'''\n",
    "print(a)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "26af92c8-e1c0-4bf5-b522-25202874ada2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " 6.What are the values of the given expressions ?\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "44a0ab53-5cc1-4821-a56c-4acfb38b0330",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "'Hello, world!'[1] **`->`**  `'e'`  \n",
    "'Hello, world!'[0:5] **`->`**  `'Hello'`  \n",
    "'Hello, world!'[:5] **`->`**  `'Hello'`  \n",
    "'Hello, world!'[3:] **`->`**  `'lo, world!'`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7f5127e0-f929-431a-9d35-bb694dc5464b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
